ISLAMABAD, Dec 13 (APP):Minister of State for Information and Broadcasting Farrukh Habib said on Monday that Imran Khan was the first prime minister who launched Health Card, the largest humanitarian project.
In a tweet, he said after Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, now every family in Punjab will be able to get free treatment up to Rs 1 million annually.The minister said that no one would remain without treatment for lack of financial resources.
